tions in [3.1.6 Normalization layers](https://namedtensor.github.io/) accept multiple named axes (e.g., two `batch,layer` axes in `BatchNorm` and one `layer` axis in `LayerNorm`). How can I define `Mean` and `Standardize` below so that they can accept different number of bound variables?\r\n\r\n```py\r\n@make_funsor\r\ndef Mean(\r\n    X: Funsor,\r\n    ax: Bound\r\n) -> Fresh[lambda X: X]:\r\n    return X.reduce(ops.add, ax) / ax.output.size\r\n\r\n@make_funsor\r\ndef Standardize(\r\n    X: Funsor,\r\n    ax: Bound\r\n) -> Fresh[lambda X: X]:\r\n    return (X - Mean(X, ax)) / (Variance(X, ax) + ops.finfo(X.data).eps).sqrt()\r\n```","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pyro-ppl/funsor/issues/485/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pyro-ppl/funsor/issues/485/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}